Ri Gwang-sik (born March 5, 1970) is a &lt;a href="North%20Korea"&gt;North Korea&lt;/a&gt;n &lt;a href="boxing"&gt;boxer&lt;/a&gt;, who won a bronze medal in the men's bantamweight (54 kg) category at the &lt;a href="1992%20Summer%20Olympics"&gt;1992 Summer Olympics&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href="Barcelona"&gt;Barcelona&lt;/a&gt;. He also captured a bronze medal at the &lt;a href="1991%20World%20Amateur%20Boxing%20Championships"&gt;1991 World Amateur Boxing Championships&lt;/a&gt;.
